FRANCE DAYBOOK: Chirac Goes on Trial; LVMH-Bulgari

-- B y  
-- 
2011-03-07T05:10:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/france-daybook-chirac-goes-on-trial-lvmh-bulgari.html
Former President  Jacques Chirac  goes
on trial on charges of having given fictitious jobs to political
supporters when he was mayor of Paris.  LVMH Moet Hennessy Louis Vuitton SA, the world’s largest
maker of  luxury goods , will take a controlling stake in Bulgari
SpA, the Financial Times reported, citing an unidentified person
close to the deal.  ALL TIMES CET  WHAT TO WATCH: GOVERNMENT:
* Former President Jacques Chirac’s trial begins. He’s charged
with giving fictitious City Hall jobs to supporters.
* President  Nicolas Sarkozy  meets with European Union Financial
Services Commissioner Michel Barnier 10:00 am.
* President Nicolas Sarkozy meets with Slovenian Prime Minister
Borut Pahor 5:00 p.m.
* Budget Minister Baroin meets with labor unions on civil
service jobs 10:30 a.m.
* Finance Minister Lagarde receives report on central banking
2:30 p.m.
* Finance Minister Lagarde meets with Agriculture Minister Bruno
Le Maire 4:15 p.m.
* Budget Minister Baroin meets with French Banking Federation
Chairman Francois Perol 5:00 p.m.
* Finance Minister Lagarde takes part in France-Israel business
conference at the OECD 6:00 p.m.  EQUITIES:
  Ciments Francais SA (CMA)  said fourth-quarter 2010 profit was 35
million euros on revenue of 976.4 million euros. The shares
gained 1.1 percent to 69.98 euros.
  Safran SA (SAF)  said it will scrap its executive and supervisory
board structure and create a single board.  MARKETS:
*The CAC 40 Index slid 1 percent to 4,020.21
*The broader SBF 120 Index retreated 0.9 percent  EARNINGS: No major earnings scheduled today  ECONOMY: No data or events scheduled today  INTERVIEWS ELSEWHERE:
-07:40 Canal Plus: Lyon Mayor Gerard Collomb
-07:50 France 2: Paris Deputy Mayor Anne Hidalgo
-08:15 LCI: UMP lawmaker Patrick Devedjian
